RADULA (n = 3). Comprises 121–125 transverse rows with 61–69 teeth per row; radular formula: (23–25)- (7–9)-1-(7–9)-(23–25). Central tooth usually symmetric, unicuspid, triangular (
Fig. 6P
). Lateral teeth longer and larger than central teeth, bicuspid, ectocone small, with sharp cusp (
Fig. 6Q
). Marginal teeth gradually changing from bicuspid to tricuspid, small endocone; mesocone large lanceolate; ectocone triangular with two to four tiny cusps (
Fig. 6R
).
